a gulf that still separates the jazz cultures on the West Coast and
the East Coast, a divide that the move of the Thelonious Monk
Institute of Jazz Performance from New England to Los Angeles had
supposedly bridged. Monk musicians performed at the Jazz Spot in
Los Angeles: From left, Bryan Lipps, Bill Mohler and Jason Goldman.
(Ed Carreon/The New York Times)
</P>
