black institutions in Mississippi now find themselves trying to
figure out how to attract more white students. Mississippi Valley -
like Jackson State and Alcorn State - is celebrating, in a reserved
sort of way, the enrollment of 103 white students (up from 5 in
1991). (Nancy Siesel/The New York Times)
