<P>
   (NYT13) NEW YORK -- April 7, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., APRIL 9 --
CAR-SMART-CUSTOMS -- Most cars imported into the United States for
use by Americans on public roads must comply with our crash-safety,
bumper-protection and pollution-control standards. Exceptions: cars
more than 25 years old, and racing or experimental cars that use
new technology. A retrofitted McLaren F1, an exotic British sports
car with 627 horsepower and a top speed in excess of 200 miles an
hour, is the inspiration for a plan to import and retrofit
thousands of Smarts. (The New York Times)
