<P>
   (NYT23) CARDAMOM MOUNTAINS, Cambodia -- April 7, 2000 --
SUB-CAMBODIA-NATURE-2 -- Now that the conflict with the Khmer Rouge
is over and the guerrillas have withdrawn from a remote corner of
Cambodia to more hospitable places, scientists are discovering a
treasure trove of rare plants and strange creatures that have been
preserved by war in a virtually pristine time capsule. Dr. Jennifer
Daltry examined a water lizard from the Cardamom Mountains. (Meng
