<P>
   (NYT16) WASHINGTON -- April 7, 2000 -- ABORTION-CARHART -- Dr.
Leroy Carhart never set out to be an abortion doctor, let alone a
crusader for abortion rights. But when the Nebraska Legislature
passed a law to ban the surgery it labeled ``partial-birth
abortion,'' Carhart sued saying the law was ``an affront to medical
practice, putting the state in between the physician and the
patient.'' The U.S. Supreme Court will hear Nebraska's appeal on
April 25. Carhart on the steps of the court earlier this week.
(Justin Lane/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT15) NAPLES, Fla. -- April 7, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., APRIL 9
-- MUTFUND-MANAGERS-2 -- Managers of three top-performing funds
talked about what drove their performance and what to make of the
market's volatile technology sector for the rest of the year. ``The
market's been going after our space,'' said Lee Kopp, 65, referring
to companies that make the equipment and software for e-commerce.
Kopp's $1.22 billion emerging-growth fund returned 42.3 percent
last quarter. (David Carson/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) AKRON, Ohio -- April 7, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., APRIL 9
-- MUTFUND-MANAGERS-1 -- Managers of three top-performing funds
