decade-old ideological wrestling match over the editorial soul of
The Forward, often described as America's best Jewish newspaper,
appears to be ending with the forced resignation of Seth Lipsky,
founding editor of the English-language weekly. ``The game is just
about over,'' said one executive at the newspaper, who said
Lipsky's departure would probably be announced early next week.
(The New York Times)
