<P>
   (NYT40) GILLETTE, Wyo. -- April 7, 2000 -- WYO-METHANE -- In
Wyoming, where low taxes and a shrinking population are causing a
bleak fiscal outlook for the state government, the scramble to
extract methane, created by the decomposition of coal, is viewed as
crucial to the state's ability to prop up its budget and so
maintain services. Forest Dunning, at a venting pipe on the
prairie, got a small taste of water that methane mining has
displaced. (Kevin Moloney/The New York Times) LITE
