everybody is thrilled by it. Methane Madness, some locals call it,
a race to some of the richest mineral deposits in North America.
But the boom is being felt all over the country as the search for
cleaner fuels reaches a fever pitch. The rapid methane development
in Wyoming, though, has set off a growing conflict between those
who say the economic benefits could help ease budget deficits and
residents who say the mining operations are damaging the land and
squandering a precious resource, clean water. By Michael Janofsky.
