1980s, urban legends were a major topic for folklore researchers.
Urban legends can travel the world by word of mouth or in print
(lately, the Internet has become a prime vehicle for their rapid
circulation and discussion). They have a persistent hold on the
imagination because they have an element of suspense or humor, they
are plausible and also have a moral. By Joyce Jensen. (725 words)
