<HEADLINE>
`SHOWING US A LOT'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Rob who?
</P>
<P>
   No, that's Not exactly the case. But Los Angeles Kings captain
Rob Blake has missed the past three games with a bruised left knee
and defenseman Jaroslav Modry has stepped in with goals in the last
two.
</P>
<P>
   Modry, who has played just 25 games this season, gave the Kings
an early lead Friday against Dallas, scoring from the slot on the
power play after a pass by Glen Murray at the 7:06 mark of the
first period.
</P>
<P>
   Modry, who has played parts of four seasons with the Kings, also
scored the club's only goal in Thursday's 1-1 tie with the
Vancouver Canucks. Modry began his career in 1993-94 with New
Jersey and played 54 games with Ottawa in 1995-96 before joining
the Kings at the end of that season.
</P>
<P>
   He entered this season with nine career goals has five already.
</P>
<P>
   ``He had a great training camp but was inconsistent earlier this
year,'' coach Andy Murray said. ``He is showing us a lot during
this opportunity.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury update: As for Blake, he hopes to play in Sunday's
regular-season finale against the Ducks in Anaheim. Blake reported
improvement skating before Friday's game.
</P>
<P>
   Ziggy Palffy, who has missed three weeks with a sprained right
shoulder, also is better. He also expects to play.
</P>
<P>
   ``That is our hope,'' Murray said. ``They both want to get in
there before the playoffs.''
</P>
<P>
   Dallas center Joe Nieuwendyk developed back spasms between the
first and second periods and did not return.
</P>
<P>
   __ False alarm: Ninety minutes before Friday's game, Los Angeles
police and firefighters were called to the northwest parking lot at
Staples Center to check out a possible bomb threat.
</P>
<P>
   A package that eventually was found only to contain soda cans
and a T-shirt caught the attention of a Staples Center employee.
Supervisors were notified, then the fire department, who called the
bomb squad.
</P>
<P>
   ``With the Democratic Convention here this summer, we are
trained not to take any precautions,'' said Lee Zeidman, vice
president for building operations. ``Neither are the police and
fire department. It was nothing, but it is important to check
everything out.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Ticket talk: Group and individual tickets for Kings playoff
games are available.
</P>
<P>
   The first two games of the opening round will be played in the
opponent's city. Game 3 will be played at the Staples Center,
presumably a week from Monday because the Lakers have a home game
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   There are 1,200 tickets available for Game 3 and 2,000 for Game
4. Ticket info: (888) KINGS LA.
</P>
</TEXT>
