</P>
<P>
   BKN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Lead item: For the third straight year,
Rick Pitino still maintains his passion about returning a hallowed
franchise back to its former glory. And for the third straight
year, the Celtics are still a reclamation project. They're not
going to the playoffs again, fueling speculation that Pitino will
be working elsewhere soon. By Mike Wise.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Lead item: When Washington Redskins
personnel men and scouts gather for their draft meetings there is
almost a giddy feel in the room. That's because they know what
every other team does: The Redskins will control the direction of
the National Football League draft. By Mike Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-NOTEBOOK (Undated) _ Lead item: Mike Caruso, Javier Valentin
and Brett Tomko spent the past two seasons in the major leagues.
All have started this season in the minor leagues. So have Joe
McEwing, Jason Johnson, Chad Allen and Doug Mientkiewicz. All
thought they had left the minors behind, but it's back to buses and
fast-food dinners. By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   For information and repeats call the News Service at
1-888-603-1036. And be sure to look for other sports stories from
our partners: The Boston Globe, Cox News Service, Hearst News
Service, The Arizona Republic, Kansas City Star, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News, San Francisco Chronicle and
Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
