   IMF-WORLDBANK _ WASHINGTON _ Advancing the spring meetings of
the International Monetary Fund and World Bank here to discuss
world economic issues. The groups that nearly shut down the World
Trade Organization meeting in Seattle are promising to the same
here ? an even bigger, brighter stage. This could either be a major
victory for the Clinton administration, or a serious black eye. The
first public battle lines over China's entry into the WTO may start
here. (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
