<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ The case a former top federal prosecutor made
for the Justice Department appointing a special prosecutor to
investigate Al Gore's political fund-raising turns out to be just
about as good a case for Attorney General Janet Reno's decision not
to. We have testimony for that from no less than the prosecutor
himself. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for Cox Newspapers.)
MOVED THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Bad news travels fast, getting faster. In
these days, it travels at cyber speed. And as we have learned when
things travel too close to the speed of light, they can become bent
and distorted. That's how lies and misinterpretations corrupt the
Internet. (Howard Kleinberg is a columnist for Cox News Service.)
MOVED THURSDAY.
