   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   THEWEST-COWBOYS _ WACO, Texas _ On the big screen, a cowboy
rides tall in the saddle, moving rhythmically against a background
of scenic vistas and towering rock. A lone Texas Ranger,
desperately outnumbered, chases bandits on horseback through canyon
and plain. A girl flirts with a cowboy in a saloon. This is
Hollywood's Old West _ a creation of film and novels sometimes as
far from the true West as it is from today's world. All of that has
little do with the realities of the cow business today. Forget that
carefree rider on horseback, said cattle aficionado Bill Bond of
Groesbeck. Real life is much more grimy. (Pierson, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   WORKING-COWBOYS _ They wear a cowboy hat for work, not dancing.
Jeans are standard issue. They drive a company truck, live in a
company house, don't have a retirement account, and can't imagine a
better life. A look at the real working cowboys of the West and
what's changed _ and what hasn't. (Grand Junction Daily Sentinel).
30. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED
</P>
