<P>
   BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKO-BASKETBALL-TRAGEDY _ On the afternoon of Sept. 16, Travis
Davenport lifted weights and shot hoops at his old high school
gymnasium. As always, his closest friends discouraged him from
joining their pick-up game. They echoed the advice of his doctors,
his pastor, his mother and other grown-ups. This time, Travis
listened, although it surely pained him. Basketball was his
passion. He played it year-round until the first in a series of
fainting spells. Even then, he occasionally would slip onto the
court. Just a few days earlier, a cardiologist had restated in no
uncertain terms that he must give up the game. So Travis, obediant,
tossed up casual jumpshots in the gym before heading south, back to
college in Cochran. That night, he collapsed and died. (Tierney,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
