<P>
   COXNET INSIDE NASCAR 0407: LAUGH TRACKS _ Now that NASCAR has
gone big-time with a mega-bucks television deal, stock-car racing
probably will get more serious. But participants in the sport still
enjoy laughing at themselves. ``Racing is like dark comedy,''
driver Kyle Petty said. ``You make fun of all the serious stuff.
You make fun of wrecks, just so you don't have to think about
them.'' (Levine, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes a
beautiful 3-column color illustration.
</P>
