<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-CELTICS-SEASONSKID-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CELTICS STEERED INTO A SKID 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL VEGA  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Two weeks ago, they were in playoff contention. They trailed
Orlando by a half-game in the race for the eighth and final spot
among Eastern Conference playoff hopefuls. But now, the season has
soured for the Celtics.
</P>
<P>
   No longer in playoff contention, they ran their losing streak to
10 with Friday night's 102-97 loss to the Philadelphia 76ers at the
FleetCenter. With six games left, including five at home, Antoine
Walker hopes the team will keep a positive frame of mind amid all
the negativity.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's very hard and it's very difficult,'' Walker conceded.
``But right now we can't afford to feel sorry for ourselves,
because this is not the way we want to end the season. This is not
the positive way to end our season. This is not the way we want our
fans to see us at the end of the season.
</P>
<P>
   ``So, for ourselves and for the fans, we definitely need to play
good basketball while we're at home, give them some good
entertaining games, and get some wins and end the season on a
positive note.''
</P>
<P>
   But there remains the very real possibility that the Celtics
could go winless the rest of the way, in which case they would
establish a club record for futility. In fact, they need only lose
four more to surpass the team-record 13-game skid set in 1994 and
matched in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   That worst-case scenario could prompt the front office to make a
major shake-up in the roster.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a good group of guys and we're better than what the
record indicates,'' Walker said. ``You don't want to tank the
season, you don't want it to go to waste, because then you force
management to shake it up, and if I was management I would shake it
up, too, if that was the case. But we've got to continue to work.
Two weeks ago, we were a half-game out of the playoffs and,
unfortunately, things went south on us.
</P>
<P>
   ``The cure for that is to get back and to play good basketball
and finish out as good as possible. Ten has got to be the magic
number that this has got to stop at. We've got to come back and get
a win Monday night.''
</P>
<P>
   The Celtics will get that opportunity when they host the Atlanta
Hawks Monday night at the FleetCenter.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just have to come in every day and work hard in practice
and come in with the right attitude,'' Walker said. ``That's the
one thing this team has done: come in with the right attitude.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not like guys don't want to be there. We want to be there
and get the work done. It makes for good basketball, because
everyone is still competitive and goes at each other and that's the
positive thing. We just got to get off this losing streak, so we
can show the fans and the organization that we're not as bad as our
record indicates.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
